Rating: 4
wonderful dish that needs to 'sit' for at least an hour for flavors to settle in. White balsamic will not dull the yellow corn, or the herbs...which are key...lots of fresh basil and flat leaf parsley. I add the tomato last or leave it out. Add a tiny bit of sugar as you saute the corn if it lacks natural sweetness.

