Rating: 3
I thought this was really tasty. I read what the other cook meant about the funny brownish color due to the balsamic vinegar, but since I'm a huge balsamic vinegar fan, I decided to brave it anyway. So yes, it was a little brown, but i thought the flavor was excellent. I didn't have any scallions; I used a lot of chopped yellow onion. And i used a lot of garlic, as well. I also added fresh basil leaves which I think is a must. Served it in bibb lettuce bedded in mixed greens wih balsamic vinegar and basil garnish. Yum. The corn had a lovely, sweet flavor to counter the vinegar (which I love anyway). Will definitely make again.

